Haghog's Handy Guide to Adding in Artifacts to CK3

Stage One: Creating an Artifact that someone owns at game start

	Follow these steps to add an artifact into the game; its setup for 

	1 - Define the template in ate-ck3\common\artifacts\templates\00_historical_artifacts_templates.txt 
		(Or one of the other template files in that folder depending on where relevant)
		Check to see if one of the templates could already work for your artifact; these templates don't need to be unique
		If making a new one:
			Copy and paste a template and define
				Can you always equip it?
				Who can benefit from it?
				What happens if you can't benefit from it? (Fallback)
				Is it unique?

	2 - Define a modifier for it in ate-ck3\common\modifiers\ate_artifact_modifiers.txt
		(Or one of the other modifier files in that folder depending on where relevant; e.g. court artifacts in their file)
			Use ones from the base game as template if you need to

	3 - Define the items visuals in ate-ck3\common\artifacts\visuals\ate_artifact_visuals.txt
		Check to see if you can use a predfined item visual; not every item needs a unique visual
			Use ones from the base game as template if you need to

	4 - Define the artifact creation effect in ate-ck3\common\scripted_effects\ate_artifacts_creation_effect.txt
		This will need to be defined for each artifact you make
			Borrow another template to model your artifact on if needed
			You'll use
				Template from step 1
				Modifier from step 2
				Visuals from step 3
			In this section

	5 - Define the localization in ate-ck3\localization\english\replace\artifacts\ate_artifacts_l_english.yml

	6 - Trigger the event to create the item in ate-ck3\events\artifacts\historical_artifacts_events.txt
		This will set it so a character has the item at the start of the game
		Look at the code around the declaration of independence to see a way of "seeding" a couple of copies of the artifact

	You should be done!

Stage Two: Setting up the artifact to be found by adventurers

	Some artifacts better work as adventure "finds" (e.g. Ark of the Covenant in base game)

	1 - Complete Steps 1 - 5 from Stage One of this Guide
		This will have your artifact setup, with the "Create artifact" effect ready to be used in-game

	2 - In Step 5, set a variable associated with the artifact in the effect
		E.g. 		
			set_variable = {
				name = example_artifact
				value = yes
			}

	3 - Find inspiration_adventure_create_artifact_effect in ate-ck3\common\scripted_effects\00_ep1_inspiration_effects.txt

	4 - Add a new option in the random_list section where #Chance of Relic is written
		This should be on the same level as the other artifacts defined here

	5 - Define
			Modifier - Modifies how likely the artifact is to be found; used to improve chances for high level adventurers/successful adventurers
			Trigger - Whether the item can be found. Lots of elements can be set here, but key elements are:
				Artifact Variable: Can be used to prevent copies of unique artifacts
					e.g.
					any_artifact = {
						NOT = {
							has_variable = example_artifact
						}
					}
				Scope:Location: Refers to where the adventurer has gone to find an artifact
					Geographical Region: Limits the item to being found in only specific regions, defined in ate-ck3\map_data\geographical_regions\geographical_region.txt
					Faith.Religion: Limit the artifact to only be found in certain faith areas
						e.g.
						scope:location ?= {
							OR = {
								geographical_region = world_us_northeast
								geographical_region = world_us_southeast
							}
							OR = {
								faith.religion = religion:americanist_religion
								faith = {
									has_doctrine = tenet_americanist_syncretism
								}
							}
						}
			Create Artifact Effect: Used to create the artifact.
				e.g.
				create_artifact_example_artifact_effect = { OWNER = root }

	This should allow the artifact to be found by adventurers and given to the player as a gift

Stage Three: Associating Character Model Accessories with Artifacts

	This will allow certain items to be visually shown on a character when equipped. We'll use the HCC Crown as an example artifact

	1 - Complete Steps 1 - 5 from Stage One of this Guide
		This will have your artifact setup, with the "Create artifact" effect ready to be used in-game

	2 - In Step 5, set a variable associated with the artifact in the effect
		E.g. 		
			set_variable = {
				name = hcc_crown
				value = yes
			}

	3 - Set a trigger that will indicate that the accessory should be shown on the character in ate-ck3\common\scripted_triggers\ate_clothing_triggers.txt
		This is only for AtE; you can create this trigger in vanilla modding
		In the case of the HCC Crown, the trigger is this
			portrait_hcc_crown_trigger = {
				exists = this
				OR = {
					AND = {
						NOT = {
							has_dlc_feature = royal_court
						}
						has_title = title:e_hcc
					}
					has_dead_character_flag = hcc_crown_wearer_dead
					any_equipped_character_artifact = {
						has_variable = hcc_crown
					}	
				}
			}
		This trigger means
			Players without Royal Court will have HCC Rulers wear the HCC Crown
			Dead Characters with the relevant Dead Character Flag will wear the HCC Crown in their image
			Characters who have the HCC Crown equipped will wear the crown correctly

	4 - Go to where the accesory you wish to associate is saved
		In the case of the HCC Crown, the accessory is saved in ate-ck3\gfx\portraits\portrait_modifiers\01_headgear_base.txt
			Adding new models is beyond the scope of this particular guide

	5 - Under the relevant artifact, set the crown to only appear when the previously set trigger is met 
		In the case of the HCC Crown, the code works in this way:
				hcc_imperial = {
					dna_modifiers = {
						accessory = {
							gene = headgear
							template = hcc_crown
							range = { 0 1 } # For the randomness to work correctly
						}
					}	
					weight = {
						base = 0
						modifier = {
							add = 200 # always pick the HCC crown over the western one
							portrait_hcc_crown_trigger = yes
						}
					}
				}
			Having a higher weight is important, or other crowns may be chosen

	Your artifact should be appearing on living characters wearing the artifact! To make this work for dead characters as well

	6 - Set the relevant dead_character_flag in ate-ck3\common\on_action\game_start.txt for any dead historical characters that should have the artifact equipped
		For the HCC Crown:
			title:e_hcc = {
				every_past_holder = {
					limit = {
						is_alive = no
					}
					add_dead_character_flag = {
						flag = hcc_crown_wearer_dead
						years = 400
					}
				}
			}
	
	7 - Add the variable associated with your artifact to artifact_visual_after_death_trigger in ate-ck3\common\scripted_triggers\ate_clothing_triggers.txt
		This trigger is only in AtE; you can create this trigger in vanilla modding

	8 - Add relevant code for your artifact to these effects in ate-ck3\common\scripted_effects\ate_scripted_effects.txt
			artifact_visual_after_death_dead_character_event_effect
				For HCC
					else_if = {
						limit = {
							any_equipped_character_artifact = {
								has_variable = hcc_crown
							}
						}
						root.primary_heir = {
							add_character_flag = {
								flag = hcc_crown
								days = 3
							}
							trigger_event = {
								id = death_management.0125
								days = 1
							}
						}
					}
			artifact_visual_after_death_dead_character_flag_effect
				For HCC
					else_if = {
						limit = {
							scope:dead_artifact_visual_heir = {
								has_character_flag = hcc_crown
							}
						}
						scope:dead_ruler = {
							add_dead_character_flag = {
								flag = hcc_crown_wearer_dead
								years = 400
							}
						}
					}

	Your artifact should appear for dead characters who die with the artifact equipped!